The paper proposes a methodology that uses reinforcement learning (RL) to achieve high performance in robots for the execution of assembly tasks. This involves optimizing control stiffness through online generation of stiffness matrices that help improve the performance of local trajectory optimization. The paper also mentions the advantage of rapid response owing to short sampling time of the trajectory planning. These aspects suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. 

Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning (RL) for task automation and optimization suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. 

The paper also mentions the use of experiments to verify the effectiveness of the proposed method, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper mentions the use of a demonstration video to showcase the performance of the proposed method, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
